 "Double 11", which means the day of Nov. 11 in Chinese, is the biggest shopping festival in the world. 2021 "#Double11" sales have set a record, with Tmall taking in 84.54 billion USD and JD receiving 54.57 billion USD. This episode of #ShowMeChina explains what is happening on "Double 11" and how it works on China's social media like #Douyin #Weibo #LittleRedbook #JD... Watch: Decode China's Social Media. Produced by Xinhua Global Service